5. Secure Secrets

Use Kubernetes Secrets
•	Store sensitive data (e.g., API keys, database credentials) in Kubernetes Secrets.
Example: Create a Secret

apiVersion: v1
kind: Secret
metadata:
  name: my-secret
type: Opaque
data:
  username: dXNlcm5hbWU= # Base64 encoded
  password: cGFzc3dvcmQ= # Base64 encoded


Use a Secret Management Tool
==============================
•	Use tools like HashiCorp Vault, AWS Secrets Manager, or Azure Key Vault to manage secrets securely.